caption: Great menu, fresh toppings. Food was great the desserts were better.
Good vegan wrap
From two Israelis that lived in the Middle East for more than 20 years this is the closest and tastiest place we have ever been too!! ‏כל הכבוד, ‏אנחנו מתים על האוכל שלכם!!!!! Soooo goooood
Gyros on Main is very good! People order it on Uber Eats a lot and I tried it. I'm Greek and have to say it's one of the better gyros I've had. Check them out. You won't regret it!
The food was amazing but the customer service was awful.  The staff acted very inconvenienced and irritated from the moment we walked in.
Very good and large portions
Gyro with feta cheese is great

This is one of the best places in town. Great, authentic, affordable Greek food. I cross the river from Cincy for the spicy Gyro and greek salad. They also have really good fries and the Chicken Shawarma is very good too. The dessert case looks excellent, but I haven't tried any of it yet. It's an instant add to the weekly rotation.
The dudes behind the counter never fail to impress!

Rude staff. After waiting patiently for five minutes no one acknowledged me so I go to every person that's sitting there for carry out and ask them if they have been taken care of. They all had. They were busy but then the guy was rude to me when I asserted myself.
The food is delicious. New hidden jem. The spicy gyro is amazing.
Great gyros, falafel, salad, hummus and baba ghanoush, dolmades, baklava, macarons, and the *best* french fries in the city. Food is fast, hot, and fresh every time we pick up.

Fries are absolutely incredible! Fluffy inside, crispy outside, and taste amazing! Falafel on pita was delicious, good texture, well seasoned and pita nice and fluffy. Sometimes falafel can be dry, but this wasn't at all. Spouse said the Philly cheese steak was quite yummy. The fried pickles weren ok, but I'd skip in the future.Nice, large portions. But again - GET THE FRIES 🙂
Always friendly and the food there is always good!
Awesome lunch specials
The best gyro place in town. Always be sure to grab the Greek fries
Absolutely fantastic! The staff was friendly and accomodating the food was perfect!!

I liked the Philly Cheesesteak sandwich, but too much oil was used in cooking. Other than that, I recommend this place. Keep in mind there is a lot of construction going on in the area and parking options are limited.
We stopped in to pick up some food last week. The food was good and we enjoyed it. The French fries were excellent.
Best falafel wrap around! Their fries are great, too. Great place to eat if you follow a vegetarian or plant-based diet.
Best gyros I've had in years.
Their Giros on Pita are amazing, try with Feta Cheese on! Falafel wasn’t that great though - but would def come back for the Gyros
Food is always wonderful but it's hard to find a parking space.
Best Gryo in Kentucky! Dynamite Greek salad... yummy.!
Incredible experience! Gyros were bursting with authentic flavor. Spicy Chicken shawarma on a pita was out of this world. Falafels were so tasty. PERFECTION!

Wow, surprised how good this place was.  Had it delivered and tasted like it was just made!  We tried the chicken shawarma platter and the gyro platter.  Loved how the gyro meat was thinly sliced and the shawarma was absolutely delicious!  The serving size is more than enough.  Also the baklava was delicious.  We will for sure order from here again.  One of my favorite gyro places!

I went in late, surprised they were open, I decided to try it instead of getting pizza yet again... Store was empty, so I got my order in. Usually when it's empty, you may get food ingredients that has been sitting around for a while. Well, they made my order fresh! I got a small gyro, which was the perfect size. Falafel which was crispy outside and moist inside, so it was perfect! The spanikopita was flakey and big & tasty! Seasoned fries were perfectly crispy yet fluffy inside. I'll definitely go back more often! Service was friendly as well!
They came with no onions or tomatoes. I called to try to find a middle ground but was told there was nothing that could be done. Never going back and that’s sad because I love gyros
I stopped in for a frozen lemonade.....it was AMAZING. Gonna go back soon to try everything else
Went to pick up a carry out order and found no masks on the cooks or other patrons. This demonstrated a lack of care that raises questions about their food safety in general.

I love this place! Best food and incredible service. Always a happy smiling face to go with some of the best food I've ever had. I can't recommend this place enough. If you haven't tried it, you NEED to!!!
None of the staff was wearing a mask. Will not eat here again nor do I recommend this place since they don't care about basic safety
Omg so good deserves better than mainstraus
Love the GYROS
Stumbled on this place in my home town excellent food and the price is very easy on the wallet thanks guys keep it up

Solid gyro place with some surprise menu items. I never would have thought of wrapping a Philly cheese steak in a tortilla and deep frying it. But it was pretty darn good. The falafel was excellent and of course the gyro was great.  Well with the visit
Plenty of meat and loaded.. tasted spot on
This is a simple shop. Good food. Great value.  Good dudes behind the counter.  Go there often.  Reward them and yourself.
Awesome Philly cheese steak, great cheese cake. Fast service!
Best gyro I have ever had!
Seriously the single best gyro in the tristate area!

I'm here at least twice a month, and the guys always take good care of me with fast, friendly, made-to-order service. As I work my way through the menu, I have yet to be disappointed. Today was no exception. I tried the Chicken Shawarma (went for the "spicy" option) and it was outstanding. Their falafel has to be the best I've ever tasted. Give this place a try.

Super poor customer service over phone. Mistakes on order. Refused to make it right. No condiments, nothing on gyro but meat, no sauce. No disposable items. Very rude when called about it, very argumentative! Through Uber Eats.

I’m hesitant to order to-go food, as it’s almost always disappointing. In the past few months I have picked up food here at least once a week, and it’s been delicious every time. Chicken is perfectly seasoned and cooked, fries are so good I have recommended friends go there just for the fries, and the veg options are awesome as well. Its great.
delicious food. Chicken Sharma and spicy gyro both were great. Hummus was solid. Get the fries, they are awesome.

I am incredibly lucky to be a 2 minute walk from this place. The food is fantastic. Burger, crispy philly, and spicy gyro are our favorites. Friendly, quality, and fast service. Small seating area inside if the world is ever allowed to dine-in again.
My Gyro was the best I ever had anywhere.  Friendly service.  Great location.  Pubs all around.  Perfect evening spot to eat.
Very nice people with AMAZING gyros!  Delicious!  Will def come back!
I was there multiple times and they closed way too early
Great gyros, nice guys, food cooked to order, hot and fresh.

We were super happy with our order! I got the chicken shawarma with fries and my Bf got the crispy philly with fries hummus and fried jalapeño poppers. All of the food was delicious and tasted fresh! Next time I want to try the crispy chicken philly!  The restaurant itself was very clean as well!

This place gets 6 out of 5 stars! Awesome food, great service, and their Baklava is the best I’ve ever had! I highly recommend and will continue to support them with carry out until we are able dine in again.
Close to home. Good gyros and tasty ff.
One of the best places to eat a Mediterranean food Very clean very friendly and very delicious
Super great gyro, fries were also great. Good vegetarian options, too. Get your gyro extra spicy.. trust me.

Very friendly and quick service! I had the gyro with feta and it was delish, perfectly cooked and the tzatziki was amazing. My husband got the spicy gyro and it wasn't crazy spicy which I was nervous about! We got the fries and they were the battered seasoned kind super fresh and crisp. We got an order or spanikopita which smelled amazing very dilly but I was too full to try it so we got them to go for later. Would definitely recommend we will be back again

This was excellent traditional spicy gyro, baba ghanoush, rice, and even the french fries (my guilty pleasure) were amazing. Next time I'm doing the grape leaves and mushrooms. Yes they have baklava. My heart is super happy. Everyone was so nice and helpful too.

The individuals working last night were so friendly - absolutely loved the service. Didn’t know what to get so I asked the two workers what their favorite thing was and ordered 1 of each and I couldn’t have been happier. We ordered the Chicken Shawarma, the Gyro Philly and of course you can’t leave without ordering some Falafels.

I wasn't aware they closed at 9 on the weekdays (which was completely my fault) I came in probably at 8:58 and was welcomed with smiles from everyone, I placed my order for dine in and the smiles still continued I didn't get a frown or a shrug like from other places, I was welcomed in to dine in and eat food, not going in to many detail but I had a very long and stressful day with work and the fact that I was greeted with smiles and not treated like I was holding them up made my evening so much better! The gyros are always top notch! Thank you to the guys behind the counter for welcoming me with smiles and not treating me like I was in the way of them closing!
Great food and fast service, the classic gyro with feta and spicy sauce was delicious!
Great gyros and great staff. Went for the first time and came back the following night. If you enjoy gyros you have to check it out. Spicy mega gyro with feta is the bomb! Fries are also amazing!

Just Ordered Gyros On Main through Uber Eats for the first time, and let me tell you, this is by far the best Gyro ive had! So much taste and great portions! The greek fries were delicious,  and even the hummice was great! Youve definitely got yourself a happy customer!
Finally got to try this place. Gyro lunch special was a LOT of food, and very very good. Looking forward to eating here again in the future!
I’ve eaten there three times, this week. The vegetable gyro with feta is fantastic. Friendly, fast service.
Friendly staff and great reasonably priced food.  They really pack on the Gyro meat!

Great experience! Classic Gyro sandwich that is a homerun! Great service as well. Made it home with a carry out order to find out that they had actually been closed for 15 minutes when we walked in, but they served us with a smile and great service. I’ll be back often!!
Have been a few times now and everything I've tried has been outstanding. Particularly fond of their falafel wrap!
falafel and gyros are incredible! eaten there 6 times in three weeks. cant wait to go again.
Rude
Outstanding, exactly what mainstrausse needs. Great carry out or dine in.
Fresh made gyros, great tzatziki, and delicious baklava! Might become a new habit.
Fresh food & great staff!
Great food and service.
What a refreshing addition to the late night scene! Fantastic gyro! I can’t wait to try more on the menu! Welcome to MainStrasse.
Just got my food right now on their opening night! Cool spot, clean, friendly, great classic gyros and falafel. Gotta check it out. Edit: Fries are fantastic
Delicious food and a really nice owner!

Delicious, juicy, flavorful gyro meat and amazing seasoned fries. Totally worth the wait on their Grand Opening! Great food, friendly staff and cool little spot in the Cov. A very nice and welcome late night spot on the weekends vs. Pizza. Please check it out, sooo good!!
